  "original_title": "\u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0bb5\u0bc7\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc1 \u0b85\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0bae\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0bae\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bc8 \u0b92\u0bb4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0bb5\u0bc7\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b8e\u0ba9 70 \u0b9a\u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bc0\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "70 percent of Sri Lankans want to abolish the executive presidential system",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "A June 2022 consolidated survey conducted by Verite Research revealed that 70 percent (+/- 2%) of the country's population is of the opinion that the executive presidential system should be abolished.",
        "Only 15 percent said they should not abolish the executive presidential system.",
        "The remaining 15 percent had other opinions (such as reducing powers rather than abolishing them altogether) or declined to comment.",
        "All age groups have expressed the same opinion. The same concept has been presented in the Southern, Eastern and Northern provinces. More than 80 percent of these provinces said they wanted the executive presidential system to be abolished.",
        "The poll was conducted as part of a survey tool coordinated by Verit\u00e9 Research. This provides an opportunity for other organizations to explore the mindset of Sri Lanka. The poll is based on responses from a nationally representative sample across the country.",
        "For this, a poll was conducted in June 2022 among 1,052 Sri Lankans above 18 years of age. It is designed to ensure that the maximum margin of error in sampling and methodology is less than 3 percent and the confidence interval is 95 percent. The poll partner is Vanguard Survey (Pvt) Ltd."
      ],
